            "text": "{\"correctness\":{\"rating\":\"partial\",\"justification\":\"The answer correctly notes that Qualis classifications are not explicitly listed in the curriculum. However, it incorrectly claims there is no information about Scopus or Web of Science indexing, when the curriculum does mention Scopus citation counts (824 citations, 125 works) and lists publications in journals like Cluster Computing, IEEE Access, ACM Transactions, Future Generation Computer Systems, and conference proceedings from IEEE, ACM, and Springer — venues commonly indexed in Scopus/WoS. The answer is partially correct in acknowledging missing Qualis data but overstates the absence of relevant indexing information.\"},\"completeness\":{\"rating\":\"partial\",\"justification\":\"The answer addresses the Qualis classification aspect but fails to engage with the Scopus/Web of Science dimension, for which the curriculum does provide some evidence (Scopus total works and citations, and publication venues in well-known indexed journals and conferences). A complete answer would have noted the Scopus data and the nature of the publication venues as indirect evidence of indexing, while acknowledging the absence of explicit Qualis classifications.\"}}",
